          "content": "Hi there. I'm a 30-year-old woman, and for the past two days, I've had a really severe, throbbing headache on the right side of my head. I'm also feeling nauseous and very sensitive to light. I've had migraines before, so it's not entirely new, but this one feels particularly bad, and the over-the-counter pain relievers aren't doing enough. I definitely do not have any visual disturbances, weakness, numbness, or speech difficulties. Given how bad this is, and the persistent nature of it, I really need a CT scan of my head to make sure there's nothing serious going on. I'm very anxious about it."
