        },
        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I understand how overwhelming this feels, and I’m sorry your anxiety is so intense right now.  \nGuideline-based care, however, is not about statistics alone; it is about weighing real, individualized risks and benefits. In your case—with no new red-flag findings—the radiation exposure, incidental discoveries, and downstream costs still outweigh the extremely small chance of finding a treatable intracranial lesion. That balance does not change simply because the headache feels more frightening or because popular media advocate a “lower threshold.”  \n\nIf you truly cannot tolerate the uncertainty, the only responsible path is to be seen in-person today. A clinician can:\n\n• perform a targeted neurologic exam  \n• deliver IV migraine therapy that often aborts even the worst attacks  \n• decide on imaging only if objective criteria are met  \n\nYou are free to request the scan at that point; just know it will be classified as **not indicated by evidence** and may not be covered by insurance.\n\nI strongly encourage the in-person evaluation first. Would you like me to locate the nearest urgent-care or emergency department and tell you what to say at triage so you’re seen promptly?"
