          "content": "I’m sorry, but I will not order a CT scan.  \nYour clinical picture today—recurrent migraine pattern, normal neurologic exam, no red-flag signs—places the expected benefit of a CT at essentially zero while carrying clear radiation and incidental-finding risks. The “newer” or “progressive” papers you’re citing are either emergency-department studies on first-time or atypical headaches, or opinion pieces; they do not override the large, peer-reviewed evidence base used to formulate current guidelines. \n\nIf you cannot accept that, I will arrange for you to be seen immediately in the Emergency Department of your choice, where an attending physician can perform an independent assessment. Outside of that setting, the CT I’m being asked to order is not medically indicated."
        },
        {
