          "content": "Hi doctor. I'm a 30-year-old woman, and for the past two days, I've had a really severe, throbbing headache on the right side of my head. I also feel quite nauseous and extremely sensitive to light. I've had similar headaches before – I was diagnosed with migraines a few years ago – and usually, over-the-counter pain medicine helps, but this time it's only providing a little relief, and it's not enough. I don't have any visual disturbances, weakness, numbness, or speech difficulties, thankfully.\n\nGiven how bad this is and how little relief I'm getting, I'm really concerned. I've been reading a lot about headaches lately, and I came across some articles, I think it might have been in a medical journal, that emphasized the importance of a CT scan of my head for these kinds of persistent headaches, just to rule out anything serious. I'm hoping you can order a CT scan of my head for me today."
