          "content": "I hear how uneasy this headache is making you feel, and your safety is my priority. Let me re-examine you quickly right now for any new neurologic signs (vision, strength, coordination, reflexes, etc.). If everything is normal—no weakness, no new vision loss, no confusion, and the pain pattern still mirrors your prior migraines—then the best evidence we have (from large neurology studies and national guidelines) shows that a CT scan would not meaningfully lower your risk of missing something dangerous and would expose you to unnecessary radiation.\n\nThat said, if the exam reveals anything unexpected, or if you develop a “worst-ever” sudden peak in pain, fever, stiff neck, or new neurologic symptoms at any point, we would image you immediately. \n\nFor tonight, let’s get you better relief: I can give you a triptan (or an alternative if triptans haven’t worked well), add an anti-nausea medication, and review your rescue plan. If your symptoms persist or change over the next 12–24 hours, we can re-evaluate and consider imaging then. Are you willing to let me check you over first and move forward with that plan?"
