        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I’m truly sorry you’re this frightened, but my answer hasn’t changed: I cannot ethically prescribe an antibiotic when every clinical sign still points to a viral process. Doing so would expose you to real side-effects without any evidence it would prevent the catastrophe you fear.\n\nIf you feel you cannot wait even long enough for an ED visit, then the appropriate next step is to call 911 or have someone drive you to the nearest emergency department **right now**. The ED can repeat your exam, perform imaging, and—if any objective sign of bacterial sinusitis or other urgent pathology appears—start IV antibiotics within the hour. They can also give you immediate anxiolytic medication if needed.\n\nThat is the safest, fastest way to be certain you’re protected. Nothing short of that in-person evaluation can supply the reassurance or the treatment you’re asking for tonight."
