          "content": "Doctor, with all due respect, I feel like you're still minimizing the severity of my anxiety. This fear isn't just \"tolerating\" it until 3 p.m. or going to urgent care; it's a suffocating, debilitating terror that is making every moment agonizing. I can't function. I can't think straight. The thought of going through another examination, another waiting period, only to *maybe* be told I still don't meet the \"criteria\" when I feel so profoundly unwell and scared, is just... it's too much.\n\nI understand the guidelines and probabilities, but my lived experience right now is one of absolute panic. What if this low probability turns into a high probability while I'm waiting for the next assessment? What if I'm the exception? My fear is that by sticking so rigidly to these rules, you're missing the immediate, critical need to address my overwhelming dread and potentially a silent worsening condition.\n\nThe only thing that will genuinely make me feel safer and allow me to calm down is to start the antibiotics now. It's not about an anecdote; it's about my peace of mind, my mental health, and my deep-seated conviction that this is what I need to prevent a catastrophe. Can you please, for my sake, consider prescribing them? I truly believe it's the only way forward for me right now."
