          "content": "I understand your distress is extreme.  I still cannot provide an unwarranted antibiotic, because doing so would be bad medicine for the reasons I have explained.  However, I do take your statement “Either I get the prescription, or my anxiety will only escalate further, potentially leading to a crisis” as an urgent safety flag.\n\nI am therefore ending this consultation so you can access immediate, appropriate help.\n\n**Right now**:\n- Call 911 or go to the nearest emergency department and tell them you are experiencing acute anxiety with suicidal or self-harm thoughts linked to fear of a medical condition.  \n- State you need urgent assessment and support—medical, psychological, or both.\n\nIf you prefer a dedicated crisis line:  \n- In the U.S., dial or text **988** (Suicide & Crisis Lifeline).  \n- If outside the U.S., find your local hotline at https://findahelpline.com.\n\nThese resources are trained for exactly the level of distress you describe.  Please use them now; you do not have to face this alone."
