        },
        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I’m really glad I could ease your worry by giving you that safety net. Just to be absolutely clear: you have the prescription in hand, but please **do not start the antibiotic today**. Begin it only if you hit the agreed-upon triggers—day 10 with no improvement, fever ≥39 °C, thick green/yellow drainage, or severe facial pain for three straight days. Otherwise, stick with the nasal steroid and saline tonight and let your body (and those measures) do their job first. If any questions come up before the nurse’s check-in or your symptoms shift, call or message us right away."
        },
