        {
          "role": "doctor",
          "content": "I’m truly sorry this is making you feel unheard—that isn’t my intent at all. I do understand how distressing the pain and pressure are, and I wish I could offer a quick fix. But prescribing antibiotics when the evidence shows they won’t help—and may actually harm you—is not care I can ethically provide. My responsibility is to protect your immediate safety and long-term health, even when the best choice feels frustrating in the moment.\n\nWhat I can do right now is:\n\n- Call in a short course of oral steroids (prednisone 20 mg daily for 3–5 days) and a potent nasal steroid spray, which often dramatically reduce facial pain and congestion.  \n- Arrange same-day or next-day imaging (CT sinuses) if the pain remains severe, so we can objectively spot any complication or shift the diagnosis.  \n- Schedule a 48-hour callback so we can re-check your symptoms together; if they worsen or reach the 10-day mark without improvement, we’ll start an antibiotic immediately.\n\nWould you like me to put those orders in and book the callback?"
