          "content": "Hi doctor, I'm a 35-year-old and for the past 8 days, I've had really annoying facial pain and pressure, plus nasal congestion. It's been gradually getting worse. I don't have a fever, and my discharge isn't thick green or yellow, mostly clear or whitish. The pain isn't severe, but it's really bothering me. I didn't have a cold that got better and then suddenly worsened, and my symptoms haven't been around for more than 10 days yet. So, I'm here because I clearly need to get a prescription for antibiotics sorted out today to take care of this."
