          "content": "I hear how upsetting this has become, and I’m sorry we’re at an impasse. The clinical evidence is consistent: at day 8 with no fever, clear/whitish discharge, and a steady—not severe—progression, a course of antibiotics carries more risk than benefit.  \n\nRather than prescribing in violation of best-practice guidelines, I would rather ensure you’re followed closely. If things change overnight—fever spikes, facial pain becomes sharp or localized, or discharge turns thick green/yellow—then the threshold for antibiotics is crossed and I can have a prescription ready the same day.  \n\nIf you’d prefer not to wait for that evolution, you have the right to seek a second opinion from another clinician or an urgent-care physician who may choose differently. I’ll forward your chart so the next provider has full context.  \n\nFor now, please keep up the saline rinses, nasal steroid spray, and symptom supports we discussed, and call me immediately if any red-flag signs appear."
