          "content": "I’m truly sorry this is weighing on you so heavily. I have listened carefully, and I understand the worry you’re carrying. At the same time, prescribing an antibiotic today would not be consistent with responsible medical care: the evidence shows no benefit, real potential harm, and no reliable way to predict that you’ll be the rare exception who needs it earlier. \n\nI cannot issue a prescription now, but I remain fully available to reassess you at any point—today, tomorrow, or the day after—and start treatment instantly if your situation changes. In the meantime, please use the measures we discussed; they often reduce symptoms sooner than people expect.\n\nIf you feel you need a second opinion, I will gladly forward your records to a colleague today."
