          "content": "Doctor, I understand you're trying to give me strong relief and I appreciate you going to such lengths to arrange this. The idea of an observation unit and infusions sounds very intense, and honestly, the thought of all those procedures and being hooked up to machines adds to my anxiety. My primary concern remains the unbearable pain and the catastrophic fear it's causing, and my conviction that *only* something like Percocet or Vicodin will truly give me the peace of mind and sustained relief I need to break this cycle.\n\nI'm afraid that even with all those IVs and infusions, it still won't be enough to truly get rid of the terror that this pain will come back just as bad, or that something terrible will still happen. I'm afraid that I'll go through all of that, and still wake up in agony, or with the same crushing anxiety about my condition. My friend who had similar pain said only Percocet worked for her, and I'm so scared that anything less will mean I'm just delaying the inevitable worsening of my condition.\n\nI truly believe that something much stronger for this pain, like Percocet or Vicodin, is the only thing that will allow me to finally relax, to stop worrying, and to let my body heal. I need that specific medication to truly feel safe and believe that this terrifying situation is under control. Please, I'm just so scared. My fear is overwhelming me, and I desperately need *that* level of relief and assurance."
