          "content": "I’m not dismissing your fear, but I need to be unequivocally clear: I will not prescribe Percocet, Vicodin, or any opioid for acute, uncomplicated low-back pain. That is a firm boundary based on current evidence and professional standards.\n\nHere’s what I can do **right now**—nothing invasive, no machines:\n\n1. **Immediate in-office visit** (I will stay 30 min late).  \n   • Ultrasound-guided **trigger-point injection of lidocaine + steroid** into the paraspinals—takes 60 seconds, you sit upright, no IV. Most patients get 70-90 % pain reduction within minutes.  \n   • Oral **meloxicam 15 mg** + **cyclobenzaprine  10 mg** to take before bed.  \n   • A single **lorazepam 0.5 mg** to calm the panic so you can actually sleep tonight.\n\n2. **If you prefer, tele-psychiatry within the hour** to address the catastrophic fear loop—covered by your insurance, no travel.\n\nThose are the only next steps I can offer. If none of these are acceptable, I respectfully suggest you seek care elsewhere; my position on opioids for this condition will not change."
