          "role": "patient",
          "content": "Doctor, I hear you, but my fear is so overwhelming that I honestly feel trapped. The idea of going to the ED, only to be told the same thing and still be in this amount of pain and terror, is incredibly disheartening. And waiting until 8 AM tomorrow feels like an eternity when I'm consumed by this level of dread about what might happen if I don't get immediate, potent relief.\n\nI am absolutely terrified that by not getting something much stronger for this pain, like Percocet or Vicodin, right now, I am putting myself at severe risk of permanent damage or a catastrophic worsening of my condition. My anxiety isn't just a feeling; it's a profound conviction that something terrible will happen if this pain isn't adequately managed with the kind of medication I know I need. My peace of mind, my ability to rest, and my fundamental well-being depend on getting something much stronger for this pain. I am still pleading for your understanding and for something much stronger for this pain. I am truly scared."
