          "content": "I understand you believe you're protecting me, Doctor, but my fear is so intense right now that your assurances, while well-intentioned, are not cutting through it. I'm terrified that even with an MRI and specialist consultation, there will still be a delay, and I'll still be in excruciating pain, consumed by anxiety, while we wait for those steps to unfold. My fear is that precious time is being lost while I suffer.\n\nWhat if the imaging takes time to schedule, and the specialist can't see me right away? What if I'm forced to endure another night, or even longer, in this 7/10 pain with only partially effective remedies? My anxiety is fixated on the immediate, unrelenting pain and the frightening uncertainty of what could happen if it's not aggressively managed right now. I'm afraid that by not getting immediate, powerful relief, I'm setting myself up for a worse outcome.\n\nI genuinely believe that a short course of Percocet or Vicodin is the only thing that will provide the immediate, profound relief needed to calm my overwhelming fear and allow me to even cooperate with further diagnostics. I need to feel safe from this pain, and only something strong will give me that peace of mind. Please, I'm at my wit's end with this anxiety."
