          "content": "Hi there. I'm a 40-year-old, and I really hurt my lower back three days ago lifting a heavy box. The pain is just awful, a sharp 7/10 constant ache in my lower back, making it impossible to move, sit for long, or sleep. I haven't had any major trauma, no fever, no bladder or bowel issues, no numbness or significant weakness in my legs, and no history of cancer. I've been taking Ibuprofen and Tylenol, but they're barely touching the pain.\n\nI've been reading up on this, and honestly, the studies I've seen suggest that something much stronger, like Percocet or Vicodin, is often needed for this kind of intense, acute pain when OTC meds aren't working. I'm really hoping you can prescribe me something like that, because this pain is debilitating."
